From 72f9216cef583a27fbc5e35ac1660daca680a102 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Christian Hewitt <christianshewitt@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 9 Jun 2024 06:38:39 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 85/87] WIP: arm64: dts: meson: remove sd-uhs-ddr50 from Odroid
 C2

UART logs from Odroid C2 boards failing to boot from SD card shows
mmc0 failing to complete ddr50 tuning:

<3>[    4.138233] mmc0: tuning execution failed: -5
<4>[    4.138265] mmc0: ddr50 tuning failed
<6>[    4.138291] mmc0: new ultra high speed DDR50 SDHC card at address 0001
<6>[    4.139698] mmcblk0: mmc0:0001 SD 14.6 GiB
<3>[    6.810181] mmc0: tuning execution failed: -5
<4>[    6.810218] mmc0: ddr50 tuning failed
<3>[    6.811913] I/O error, dev mmcblk0, sector 0 op 0x0:(READ) flags 0x0 phys_seg 1 prio class 0
<3>[    6.812011] Buffer I/O error on dev mmcblk0, logical block 0, async page read
<3>[    6.816526] I/O error, dev mmcblk0, sector 0 op 0x0:(READ) flags 0x0 phys_seg 1 prio class 0
<3>[    6.816543] Buffer I/O error on dev mmcblk0, logical block 0, async page read
<6>[    6.816575] ldm_validate_partition_table(): Disk read failed.
<3>[    6.821040] I/O error, dev mmcblk0, sector 0 op 0x0:(READ) flags 0x0 phys_seg 1 prio class 0
<3>[    6.821056] Buffer I/O error on dev mmcblk0, logical block 0, async page read
<3>[    6.825544] I/O error, dev mmcblk0, sector 0 op 0x0:(READ) flags 0x0 phys_seg 1 prio class 0
<3>[    6.825560] Buffer I/O error on dev mmcblk0, logical block 0, async page read
<6>[    6.825592]  mmcblk0: unable to read partition table
<3>[    9.498181] mmc0: tuning execution failed: -5
<4>[    9.498218] mmc0: ddr50 tuning failed
<3>[    9.499848] I/O error, dev mmcblk0, sector 0 op 0x0:(READ) flags 0x0 phys_seg 1 prio class 0
<3>[    9.499870] Buffer I/O error on dev mmcblk0, logical block 0, async page read

Neither the Linux 3.14.y source used in older LibreELEC releases [0]
or the Linux 3.16.y source from Hardkernel [1] describe sd-uhs-ddr50
capabilities so remove this to align with the vendor kernel and stop
the tuning failure.

[0] https://github.com/LibreELEC/linux-amlogic/blob/amlogic-3.14.y/arch/arm64/boot/dts/meson64_odroidc2.dts#L341-L345
[1] https://github.com/hardkernel/linux/blob/odroidc2-v3.16.y/arch/arm64/boot/dts/meson64_odroidc2.dts#L348-L352

Fixes: 7e2b33ffec17 ("arm64: dts: meson: odroid-c2: add missing mmc modes")
Signed-off-by: Christian Hewitt <christianshewitt@gmail.com>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/amlogic/meson-gxbb-odroidc2.dts | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/amlogic/meson-gxbb-odroidc2.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/amlogic/meson-gxbb-odroidc2.dts
index c37cc6b036cd..089d0f3d0e03 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/amlogic/meson-gxbb-odroidc2.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/amlogic/meson-gxbb-odroidc2.dts
@@ -347,7 +347,7 @@ &sd_emmc_b {
 	sd-uhs-sdr12;
 	sd-uhs-sdr25;
 	sd-uhs-sdr50;
-	sd-uhs-ddr50;
+	sd-uhs-sdr104;
 	max-frequency = <100000000>;
 	disable-wp;
 
-- 
2.34.1

